  <front>
   <head>ODE to CUPID on VALENTINE'S Day.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">COME thou rosy-dimpled boy,</l>
     <l n="2" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Source of ev'ry heart-felt joy,</l>
     <l n="3" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Leave the blissful bow'rs awhile,</l>
     <l n="4" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Paphos and the Cyprian isle:</l>
     <l n="5" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Visit Britain's rocky shore,</l>
     <l n="6" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Britons too thy pow'r adore.</l>
     <l n="7" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Britons hardy, bold, and free,</l>
     <l n="8" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Own thy laws, and yield to thee.</l>
     <l n="9" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Source of ev'ry heart-felt joy,</l>
     <l n="10" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Come thou rosy-dimpled boy.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="11" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Haste to Sylvia, haste away,</l>
     <l n="12" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">This is thine, and Hymen's day;</l>
     <l n="13" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Bid her thy soft bondage wear,</l>
     <l n="14" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Bid her for Love's rites prepare.</l>
     <l n="15" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Let the nymphs with many a flow'r</l>
     <l n="16" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Deck the sacred nuptial bow'r.</l>
     <l n="17" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Thither lead the lovely fair,</l>
     <l n="18" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">And let Hymen too be there.</l>
     <l n="19" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">This is thine, and Hymen's day,</l>
     <l n="20" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Haste to Sylvia, haste away.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="21" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Only while we love we live,</l>
     <l n="22" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Love alone can pleasure give;</l>
     <l n="23" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Pomp and pow'r, and tinsel state,</l>
     <l n="24" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Those false pageants of the great,</l>
     <l n="25" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Crowns and scepters, envied things,</l>
     <l n="26" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">And the pride of Eastern kings,</l>
     <l n="27" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Are but childish empty toys,</l>
     <l n="28" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">When compar'd to Love's sweet joys,</l>
     <l n="29" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Love alone can pleasure give,</l>
     <l n="30" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Only while we love, we live.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
